<subSubSection pageId="345" pageNumber="346" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="345" pageNumber="346">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="345" pageNumber="346">
This European and North African subspecies is adventive in North America where it is known from Maine (Larochelle and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="LariviÃ¨re">Lariviere</normalizedToken>
1990a: 28, 33, as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1760" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Asaphidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="345" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="345" pageNumber="346">Asaphidion flavipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and southeastern New Hampshire (Bell 1989b: 204, as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1760" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Asaphidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="345" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="345" pageNumber="346">Asaphidion flavipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) to Long Island, New York (Davidson and Langworthy 1981: 280, as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1760" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Asaphidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="345" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="345" pageNumber="346">Asaphidion flavipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The first inventoried specimens collected on this continent were found in the late 1920s in Long Island (Cooper 1930: 21, as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1760" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Asaphidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="345" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="345" pageNumber="346">Asaphidion flavipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the next ones were found in 1976 also on Long Island (Davidson and Langworthy 1981: 280).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
